         <description>Belonie Scioneaux was born in 1931 in Vacherie, Louisiana, the son of
            Ernest and Martha Scioneaux. His family was employed by a plantation on which they
            lived, and he began working at a young age. As an adult he worked at Avondale Shipyard
            for a time before leaving because of health problems. He married at least twice (second
            wife: Audrey Kraemer Scioneaux), and had several children and stepchildren. Scioneaux, a
            native French speaker and resident of Chackbay, enjoyed hunting and helping at his
            daughter's restaurant, Nocko's Deli, until his death in 2011.</description>
